00:52:31.540 --> 00:52:40.589
One of my personal goals is to make general
operating grants even sexier than program

00:52:40.589 --> 00:52:47.829
grants, because program funds are the single
easiest funds for any non-profit to raise

00:52:47.829 --> 00:52:58.430
primarily because if you do a bit of research
you can connect directly with a teen, a troubled

00:52:58.430 --> 00:53:06.219
at risk youth, who you're helping to get an
education or a family that you're helping

00:53:06.219 --> 00:53:13.069
through providing transitional housing to
or a specific number of individuals who are

00:53:13.069 --> 00:53:17.170
getting treatment for a particular disease.

00:53:17.170 --> 00:53:25.670
But in reality none of those programs would
even exist if organizations did not have the

00:53:25.670 --> 00:53:32.950
general operating funds that provides the
core infrastructure for all of their service

00:53:32.950 --> 00:53:33.950
provisions.

00:53:33.950 --> 00:53:40.289
At SV2, the Silicon Valley Social Venture
Fund, we actually only give organizational

00:53:40.289 --> 00:53:48.019
capacity building grants and we do that primarily
because those are the single hardest funds

00:53:48.019 --> 00:53:50.269
to raise.

00:53:50.269 --> 00:53:56.119
The only type of grants that my husband and
I give through all of our philanthropy, and

00:53:56.119 --> 00:54:02.390
same with my family's philanthropy, are general
operating grants.

00:54:02.390 --> 00:54:13.819
So I would encourage you to understand the
impact that a non-profit has, but don't impose

00:54:13.819 --> 00:54:24.579
your personal needs or ego or idea of what
the organization needs on that organization;

00:54:24.579 --> 00:54:29.519
make an investment in the leadership team
